snippet: South Korea’s defense chief said on Thursday that the missile possessed “considerable” range, but that it was not capable of reaching the United States.
abstract: South Korea's defense chief says that North Korea has moved missile with considerable range to its east coast, but that weapon is not capable of reaching United States; disclosure comes as North's military warns it is ready to strike American military forces with 'cutting-edge nuclear means'.
lead_paragraph: South Korea’s defense chief said on Thursday that the missile possessed “considerable” range, but that it was not capable of reaching the United States.
